      • EntryBox

        EntryBox(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Composite shell,
        java.lang.Object entryBoxLayoutData,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color borderColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color entryBoxBackgroundColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color entryBackgroundColor,
        java.lang.String[] entryTitles,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color labelForegroundColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color labelBackgroundColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Font labelFont,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color textForegroundColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color textBackgroundColor,
        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Font textFont)
        Creates a composite within the input shell. This contains (entrytitles.length) Entrys (Objects that extends Composites). Each Entry has a Label and a Text (textbox), and the input parameters define every Entry. Each Entry's Label displays a String within the input String[] entryTitles. The Entrys are displayed vertically, in the same order as their Label's String within entryTitles, with smaller indices north of greater indices.
        Parameters:
        shell - The shell to contain this.
        entryBoxLayoutData - The desired LayoutData for this.
        borderColor - The desired color for the border of this.
        entryBoxBackgroundColor - The desired color for the background of this.
        entryBackgroundColor - The desired color for the backgrounds of the Entry's.
        entryTitles - The desired titles for the Entrys
        labelForegroundColor - The desired foreground of the Entrys' Labels.
        labelBackgroundColor - The desired background of the Entrys' Labels.
        labelFont - The desired Font of the Entrys' Labels.
        textForegroundColor - The desired foreground of the Entrys' Texts.
        textBackgroundColor - The desired background of the Entrys' Texts.
        textFont - The desired Font of the Entrys' Text.
